Park. Download the waiver from https://www.cityofsacramento.org/ParksandRec/Parks/Park-Directory/North-Natomas/ValleyOakPark and submit your dog profile before your visit.\",\"lastUpdated\":\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\"},{\"question\":\"How does pricing work at Valley Oak Park?\",\"answer\":\"Valley Oak Park offers flexible memberships and punch cards so you can tailor visits to your routine. Contact the desk for the latest promotions or multi-dog discounts.\",\"lastUpdated\":\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\"},{\"question\":\"Which amenities does Valley Oak Park offer?\",\"answer\":\"The team rotates toys, agility props, and splash features weekly so repeat visits to Valley Oak Park never feel stale. Expect shaded seating, rinse stations, and staff roaming the yards to keep playgroups safe.\",\"lastUpdated\":\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\"},{\"question\":\"When is Valley Oak Park open and where do I park?\",\"answer\":\"Hours rotate with weather and staffing, so call ahead to confirm current play blocks. Street and shared-lot parking is available nearby; arrive a few minutes early to grab a spot. Use posted signage around Sacramento to navigate any temporary closures.\",\"lastUpdated\":\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\"},{\"question\":\"How do I contact the team at Valley Oak Park?\",\"answer\":\"For reservations, temperament assessments, or party rentals, call (916) 808-5200, and visit https://www.cityofsacramento.org/ParksandRec/Parks/Park-Directory/North-Natomas/ValleyOakPark. The concierge team at Valley Oak Park typically replies within one business day.\",\"lastUpdated\":\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\"}],\"source\":\"static\",\"listingType\":\"free\"}],\"cityName\":\"Sacramento\",\"topAmenities\":[]}]}]}]\n16:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"className\":\"city-comparison-section\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L40\",null,{\"parks\":\"$15:props:children:props:c